# Rockport Trivy ignores — intentional architecture decisions
# Review periodically to ensure these are still valid

# Egress to 0.0.0.0/0 required: instance needs outbound to Bedrock API + Cloudflare tunnel
AVD-AWS-0104

# CloudWatch log group KMS — default encryption sufficient for non-sensitive idle-check logs
AVD-AWS-0017

# Lambda X-Ray tracing — not worth the cost for a simple 5-min cron checker
AVD-AWS-0066

# S3 video bucket uses SSE-S3 (AES256) not CMK — Bedrock writes directly to this bucket,
# contents are ephemeral (7-day lifecycle), and CMK adds unnecessary cost/complexity
AVD-AWS-0132

# S3 bucket logging disabled — artifacts bucket is internal-only, video buckets are ephemeral
# (7-day lifecycle). A dedicated log bucket adds cost for minimal audit value
AVD-AWS-0089

# S3 versioning disabled on video buckets — write-once ephemeral output auto-deleted after 7 days,
# versioning would double storage costs for throwaway data
AVD-AWS-0090

# CloudTrail KMS — default SSE-S3 encryption sufficient for management event audit logs,
# CMK adds cost and IAM complexity with no practical security benefit for this use case
AVD-AWS-0015

# CloudTrail CloudWatch logging — S3-based logging is sufficient for post-incident
# investigation. CloudWatch adds cost (per-GB ingestion) and IAM complexity for
# real-time alerting that isn't needed on a personal proxy project
AVD-AWS-0162

# IAM policy s3:* wildcard — flagged in the rockport-deploy-role permissions
# boundary in iam-operator-roles.tf. The boundary is an UPPER BOUND, not a grant:
# the actual S3 permissions come from terraform/deployer-policies/monitoring-storage.json
# which is resource-scoped to rockport-tfstate-*, rockport-artifacts-*, rockport-video-*
# buckets only. Boundaries are coarse by design (every other service in the same
# boundary — ec2:*, ssm:*, lambda:*, logs:*, events:*, cloudwatch:*, etc. — also uses
# wildcards). Tightening to enumerate every S3 action would require maintaining a list
# that drifts from AWS's evolving API while gaining no real security benefit beyond
# what the resource-scoped attached policy already provides.
AVD-AWS-0345
